---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Amit Srivatsa"
  description="Privacy policy for amitsrivatsa.com — how data is collected, used, and protected under GDPR."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-white pt-32 pb-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

      <div class="mb-12">
        <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-[10px] font-bold text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-6">
          Legal
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Last updated: February 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-gray-900 prose-p:text-gray-600 prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-a:text-black prose-a:underline hover:prose-a:text-orange-600 prose-li:text-gray-600">

        <p>
          This privacy policy explains how Amit Srivatsa ("I", "me") collects and uses data when you visit
          <strong>amitsrivatsa.com</strong>. I respect your privacy and comply with the
          General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
        </p>

        <h2>1. What data is collected</h2>
        <p>
          With your consent, I use <strong>Google Analytics 4 (GA4)</strong> to understand how visitors
          use this website. GA4 collects:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pages visited and time spent on each page</li>
          <li>Referring website or search engine</li>
          <li>Approximate location (country/city level, derived from IP address)</li>
          <li>Device type, browser, and operating system</li>
          <li>A randomly generated analytics identifier stored in a cookie (<code>_ga</code>)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          No names, email addresses, or other directly identifying personal data are collected through analytics.
          If you contact me via email or book a consultation, your email address is handled directly by the
          respective services (Outlook, Google Calendar) and is not shared.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Purpose and legal basis</h2>
        <p>
          Analytics data is used solely to understand which content is most useful and to improve the website.
          The legal basis for this processing is your <strong>consent</strong> (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a)).
          Analytics are only activated after you click "Accept" on the cookie banner.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          If you accept analytics, Google Analytics sets the following cookies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>_ga</code> — distinguishes unique users; expires after 2 years</li>
          <li><code>_ga_XXXXXXXXXX</code> — stores session state; expires after 2 years</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Your consent choice is stored in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> under the key
          <code>cookieConsent</code>. This is not a cookie and is never sent to any server.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          Google Analytics retains event data for <strong>14 months</strong> by default, after which it is
          automatically deleted.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Third-party processor: Google</h2>
        <p>
          Analytics data is processed by Google LLC, which may transfer data to servers in the United States.
          Google participates in the EU–US Data Privacy Framework.
          See Google's privacy policy at{' '}
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            policies.google.com/privacy
          </a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          No other third parties receive your data from this website.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Your rights under GDPR</h2>
        <p>As an EU resident, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of data held about you</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — request deletion of your data</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — request correction of inaccurate data</li>
          <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a portable format</li>
          <li><strong>Object</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> — withdraw analytics consent at any time (see below)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact me at{' '}
          <a href="mailto:amitsrivatsa@outlook.com">amitsrivatsa@outlook.com</a>.
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Dutch data protection authority,
          the <a href="https://www.autoriteitpersoonsgegevens.nl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens
          </a>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Withdrawing consent</h2>
        <p>
          You can withdraw your analytics consent at any time. This stops future data collection
          but does not delete data already collected.
        </p>
        <p>
          <button
            id="withdraw-consent"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-5 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white bg-black border border-black rounded-full hover:bg-gray-800 transition-all cursor-pointer"
          >
            Withdraw consent
          </button>
        </p>
        <script is:inline>
          document.getElementById('withdraw-consent').addEventListener('click', function() {
            localStorage.removeItem('cookieConsent');
            window.location.reload();
          });
        </script>

        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy? Email me at{' '}
          <a href="mailto:amitsrivatsa@outlook.com">amitsrivatsa@outlook.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Data controller:</strong> Amit Srivatsa, Almere, Netherlands.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
